    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe `@markup.heading.*` capture extends to the block quote continuation line.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\n2. `:set ft=markdown`\n3. Enter text into buffer:\n      ```markdown\n      > # heading\n      > text\n      ```\n4. Place cursor on first or second character of the second line, i.e. `>  `.\n5. `:Inspect`\n\nOutput includes `@markup.heading.1.markdown`:\n\n```\nTreesitter\n  - @markup.quote.markdown links to Special   priority: 90   language: markdown        \n  - @markup.heading.1.markdown links to Title   priority: 100   language: markdown     \n  - @punctuation.special.markdown links to Special   priority: 100   language: markdown\n```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nOutput should not include `@markup.heading.1.markdown`, e.g.:\n\n```\nTreesitter\n  - @markup.quote.markdown links to Special   priority: 90   language: markdown        \n  - @spell.markdown links to @spell   priority: 100   language: markdown               \n  - @punctuation.special.markdown links to Special   priority: 100   language: markdown\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-631+ga5d4b4e0fc\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot version: 1.27.0 +pgo +ime +graphemes +toplevel-tag +blur -assertions\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
