        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I see, I will report it upstream then.\n\n@clason CommonMark shows headings nested inside block quotes in the current spec [here](https://spec.commonmark.org/0.31.2/#block-quotes), and I've seen it used in several other places, like [in the Markdown Guide](https://www.markdownguide.org/basic-syntax/#blockquotes-with-other-elements). According to which spec or implementation is it not proper Markdown? Are you thinking of a specific one?",
